* reaction.manifestation from http://hl7.org/fhir/ValueSet/clinical-findings (example)
* reaction.manifestation ^comment = "Manifestation can be expressed as a single word, phrase or brief description. For example: nausea, rash or no reaction. It is preferable that manifestation should be coded with a terminology, where possible. The values entered here may be used to display on an application screen as part of a list of adverse reactions, as recommended in the UK NHS CUI guidelines.  Terminologies commonly used include, but are not limited to, SNOMED CT or ICD10."
